<TEXT>
pat geiger known around town as 
the elvis lady has spent the past seven years keeping elvis 
presley alive 
elvis the postage stamp that is 
from the kitchen table of her tidy comfortable home on route 
10 geiger runs the elvis postage stamp campaign her goal is 
to convince the us postal service to give the king its stamp 
of approval 
without question elvis presley is the perfect subject for a 
us commemorative postage stamp geiger said he was and even 
though he left us 13 years ago continues to be one of this 
countrys greatest goodwill ambassadors 
her devotion may pay off a postal service official says elvis 
is indeed still alive in a postal sense 
theres a very good chance that sometime in the future there 
will be an elvis stamp said frank thomas a postal service 
marketing specialist in washington dc personally i think 
there will be 
the major obstacle for a presley postage stamp is concern over 
the lifestyle issue thomas said the postal service has received 
mail complaining that honoring a known drug abuser sends a bad 
message to americas youth he said 
but geiger scoffs at that notion pointing to other stamp 
subjects with controversial private lives presley stamps already 
have been issued in at least seven countries including west 
germany she said 
since beginning her campaign in 1983 geiger said she has gone 
through five postmasters general and is now on her sixth anthony 
frank 
frank reportedly said soon after taking office that he supports 
an elvis stamp but after the ensuing outcry over presleys 
welldocumented drug abuse the king died of an overdose in 1977 
frank retreated and said the issue requires further review 
his wavering prompted geiger to publicly call him a wimp 
it also renewed her determination to honor the man she credits 
with changing her life 
i will not give up until either elvis gets his stamp or i die 
whichever comes first the 70yearold greatgrandmother said 
over a lunchtime beer 
to understand the extent of geigers passion for presley one 
must visit her house it is walltowall and floortoceiling 
elvis posters line every wall most highlighting presleys 1970s 
jumpsuit phase 
bookcases are stuffed with presley tomes both reverential and 
scandalous shelves burst with videocassettes of presley movies 
and photo albums hold thousands of pictures thats not including 
her records and tapes 
the first presley picture geiger bought a blackandwhite shot 
taken at a 1969 press conference will be buried with her she vows 
pictures are my addiction geiger said then adds pardon 
me evis for using that word 
presleymania came late in geigers life although her older son 
dressed in pink and black in the 1950s to emulate presley geiger 
did not convert until a 1968 tv show known as the comeback 
special 
i looked at that man in that black leather suit and said 
phew geiger said i sat in that chair and said nobody is 
that good looking it was kind of sudden i was never the same 
after that night 
the postage stamp entered her life in 1983 when a fellow 
presley fan mentioned the idea after some investigating geiger 
learned ordinary citizens are not eligible for stamp consideration 
until 10 years after their deaths 
so geiger spent the next several years laying the groundwork for 
her big 1987 push 
i thought it would be a simple thing she said boy was i 
naive 
postal service officials have come to know geiger well thomas 
said she is in fact one of their best customers firing off 
letters to anybody connected with the agency 
you name em ive written to em she said waving a wrist 
adorned with an elvis presley watch 
commemorative postage stamps are nominated by the 15member 
citizens stamp advisory committee which meets every two months 
and then must be approved by the postmaster general thomas said 
although presley has been eligible for three years he still has 
not been chosen for the honor does this mean elvis the stamp 
is dead 
no not at all thomas said 
the committee might include presley in a stamp series on 
american musicians but that doesnt sit well with geiger 
elvis was one of a kind there will never be another she 
said he does not fit into a group 
the committee will announce next years commemorative stamps 
within a month thomas said 
if they dont announce it that doesnt mean it wont show up 
in 1991 he said the fact that theyre spending so much time 
on the subject is a positive sign 
meanwhile geiger waits impatiently and spends her days mostly 
on presleyrelated matters there are the constant letters from 
supporters around the world the radio appearances the newspaper 
interviews 
how did i get here i absolutely do not know she said 
next to my children hes the most important person in my life i 
dont know what id do if there wasnt an elvis 
</TEXT>
