<TEXT>
get ready for a plateful of soul more hot 
sounds from hotlanta 
atlanta in the 1990s is emerging as the new center for rhythm 
and blues just as detroit did in the 60s with motown 
recording artists are flocking to the souths capital from new 
york and los angeles drawn by a cheaper real estate market and 
more privacy 
atlanta was one of the countrys bestkept secrets said tom 
wright owner of cheshire sound studios where singers such as 
peabo bryson and bobby brown come to record not anymore 
bryson was new in the music business and atlanta seemed like a 
good place to start so when the relatively unknown bang records 
offered him a contract he snapped it up nineteen years later 
hes still here after raising a family and building a prosperous 
career 
atlanta was not a throbbing metropolis full of opportunity in 
the recording industry but it was also not a new york city all 
crowded bryson said in an interview 
i wanted to develop my writing style here learn to make 
recordings now the producers are here the equipment is here im 
glad i stayed 
bryson was joined last year by brown the former new edition 
member whose multiplatinum album dont be cruel sst bakes under the 
summer sun winter is arriving in earnest in southern australia 
with heavy snowfalls high winds and hail causing traffic havoc in 
some areas 
in sydney strong winds uprooted trees and snapped power lines 
on wednesday night cutting power to hundreds of families in the 
citys north and southeast marine police were kept busy on sydney 
harbor after boats broke their moorings 
some highways were closed by snow and sleet in highland areas of 
new south wales victoria and tasmania states 
a weather bureau spokesman said the high temperature was just 49 
degrees in melbourne on wednesday the citys lowest june maximum 
in four years 
a gale warning was in effect for all victorian and tasmanian 
coastal waters some areas reported winds of up to 60 mph on 
wednesday night 
heavy snowfalls and blizzards were reported at ski resorts in 
northeastern victoria state and more rough weather was in the 
forecast 
a spokesman for the bureau of meteorology in tasmania an island 
state off australias southern coast said temperatures in the 
capital hobart had dipped almost 9 degrees below average to a 
minimum of 36 degrees 
</TEXT>
