<TEXT>
construction workers excavating a 
building site near parliament dug out a mound of rubble containing 
a 2200pound us bomb but didnt discover the live world war 
ii relic until later officials say 
the bomb went undetected tuesday until it was being unloaded at 
a dump site along the highway connecting bonn to cologne city 
officials in cologne said it had been driven in a dump truck from 
the construction site through bonn 
bomb experts were immediately called sealed off the area and 
safely defused the bomb 
according to an aerial photograph of the construction site 
officials said the bomb had been buried about 12 feet deep in what 
is now the government center of bonn 
since the end of world war ii thousands of tons of unexploded 
bombs and other munitions left over from the war have been 
uncovered in germany and bomb experts are regularly called out to 
defuse them to prevent injuries to the public 
