the government has extended a state of 
emergency for 60 more days in a third of the perus territory 
giving the military broad powers to fight leftist guerrillas 
the move comes a month before alberto fujimoris inauguration as 
president and affects eight states and one province peru is 
divided into 24 states which are subdivided into provinces 
the state of emergency applies to the states of apurimac 
ayacucho huancavelica junin pasco huanuco san martin and 
ucayali it also covers ucayali province in loreto state 
the decree puts the areas in perus central and southern 
highlands and northern jungle under military control and allows 
authorities to restrict freedom of movement detain people without 
charge and conduct searches without warrants 
lima the capital and home to a third of perus 22 million 
people also is under a state of emergency but it is administered 
by the national police 
political violence related to the decadeold shining path 
insurgency has killed more than 18500 people 
the government first imposed the state of emergency in december 
1982 in ayacucho birthplace of the rebel movement the measure has 
since been steadily extended to other areas as the rebel violence 
has expanded 
