countries hit by unrelenting 
waves of vietnamese refugees are getting tougher the boat people 
increasingly face being pushed back to sea or returned to this 
communist land they risked their lives to flee 
aid officials say malaysia took in more than 16000 vietnamese 
in 1989 but rebuffed about 8700 others in the past year 
indirectly causing some deaths 
other southeast asian nations implicity have threatened the same 
unless the united states by july 1 stops opposing the forced 
repatriation of those vietnamese judged to be economic migrants 
more than 117000 vietnamese refugees fill camps in the region 
it is now the 11th hour for the vietnamese boat people rep 
hamilton fish rny told a congressional hearing on june 21 
if first asylum is to be retained it must be at the 
uncomfortable price of reexamining the question of involuntary 
repatriation 
despite the increasing hostility there appears little letup in 
the exodus of more than 15 million people since the communists 
