<TEXT>
here are key facts about the hubble space 
telescope 
size 425 feet long 14 feet diameter telescope barrel 
weight 25500 pounds 
launched april 24 1990 aboard space shuttle discovery placed 
in 381mile orbit the next day by astronauts 
purpose to study the universe with the most powerful telescope 
ever placed in orbit designed to give views of celestial objects 
25 times fainter than the faintest seen from earth unobstructed by 
the earths atmosphere 
instruments faint object camera faint object spectrograph 
goddard high resolution spectrograph high speed photometer wide 
field planetary camera 
planned lifetime 15 years 
powered solarpowered batteries 
communications radio control from the goddard space flight 
center in maryland signals relayed through tracking and data relay 
satellites 
light collection 945 inch primary mirror reflects to 122inch 
secondary mirror mirrors are set precisely 16 feet apart light is 
distributed through other mirrors and optics to five instruments 
and to fine guidance sensors that aim telescope data is 
transmitted to earth as electronic signal visible light data is 
reformed into images by computer 
history approved by congress in 1977 prepared for launch in 
1986 delayed by challenger explosion 
manufacturer mirrors and telescope assembly by perkinelmer 
co now hughes danbury optical systems inc of danbury conn a 
subsidiary of general motors corps hughes aircraft unit lockheed 
missiles and space company inc designed and built the spacecraft 
module and assembled and tested the entire craft 
cost 15 billion for the spacecraft 300 million for ground 
operations 300 million for manufacture and testing of servicing 
equipment 
</TEXT>
