<TEXT>
huge going out of business sale banners 
plastered across the display windows of garfinckels department 
store obscured the mannequins in stylish black cocktail dresses and 
upscale beachwear 
carole melham was shocked shes been shopping at garfinckels 
since she was a little girl growing up in suburban chevy chase md 
i just cant imagine they could let this happen she said 
standing on the sidewalk in 80degree heat waiting for the doors to 
open wednesday 
its symbolic of a lost era like the paris of the 1920s 
she said i was raised on garfinckels shopping was a major 
event my mother bought me tons and tons of things here i remember 
when there was a doorman to greet you 
it was another world i loved the atmosphere the high 
ceilings the elevators the sales clerks whod look for good buys 
and set things aside for you garfinckels stayed oldfashioned 
and it never went down the tubes it was a very classy store 
all thats left are congested malls in the suburbs where 
everyone chews gum the merchandise has gotten so bad the big 
stores its like shopping in a zoo or a barn its so raunchy the 
world has changed its all very depressing 
garfinckels an elegant washington landmark for 85 years 
announced last week it was seeking protection from creditors in 
federal bankruptcy court and closing seven of its nine stores 
including its flagship downtown emporium at the busy intersection 
of 14th and f streets 
retail industry analysts said garfinckels had fallen victim to 
aggressive competition from bloomingdales neimanmarcus 
nordstrom and other large national department stores that have 
muscled into washingtons affluent suburbs in recent years 
garfinckels troubles were compounded by a succession of five 
owners whose conflicting marketing strategies confused and 
disappointed their traditional customers who included the rich and 
powerful of washington many of them took their business elsewhere 
the liquidation sale is intended to clear garfinckels store 
shelves and display cases of all merchandise valued at 22 
million within 60 days under a courtapproved deal an estimated 
9 million to 10 million of the sale proceeds is expected to go 
directly to one of garfinckels principal secured creditors 
mrs melham and her small son timothy were among hundreds of 
whitegloved matrons their yuppie offspring and eager bargain 
hunters who swarmed through garfinckels polished bronze doors at 
noon wednesday 
they snapped up garfinckels trademark luxury items waterford 
crystal hermes scarves countess mara silk ties godiva 
chocolates givenchy pantyhose and christofle silverware at a 20 
percent discount 
within 15 minutes the front doors were ordered closed 
temporarily to contain the throng a short time later two of 
garfinckels woodpaneled elevators jammed under the crush of 
shoppers trying to get upstairs 
i feel so very sad said gertrude hallila 72 who has been 
a loyal customer since she arrived in washington during world war 
ii she remembers riding the trolley with her children for a day at 
garfinckels with lunch in the greenbrier room 
maria kostecka who lives in the posh suburb of potomac md 
said she was extremely upset over garfinckels demise 
she liked the excellent clothes the dignified atmosphere 
no shoving or pushing in the spacious aisles and the very 
classy saleswomen 
they would call my home and tell me about a forthcoming 
sale she recalled they knew my size and theyd say they were 
holding a dress they thought id like if i returned something two 
months later they would take it back with a smile little things 
like that mean a lot 
mildred pickett remembers moving to racially segregated 
washington to work for the government in 1942 she was a young 
black stenographer from canton ill and a stranger to 
discrimination 
years ago it was said negroes couldnt come to 
garfinckels she recalled but if you dressed well and carried 
yourself well they would accept some people depending on the 
clerk i never felt uncomfortable coming to a store like 
garfinckels the quality was very good and all the clerks were 
courteous and businesslike why the blouse im wearing today i 
bought on sale here 18 years ago 
</TEXT>
