<TEXT>
bowling long ago shed its fred flintstone image 
and its wide appeal is no more apparent than at marigold bowl 
theres a japanese league a puerto rican league a janitors 
league and a gay league about every variety of race religion 
occupation and ethnic background is represented at the 32lane 
alley near the chicago cubs wrigley field 
were a league of nations our customers are diversified 
said owner bob fagenholz 54 
theres even a league called the marigold straits 
we had a gay league bowling in front of us and another after 
us we just wanted to define ourselves but we spell it 
differently said fred schmidt an architect 
