<TEXT>
the earthquake that devastated this town of 
40000 people has quadrupled the size of its main cemetery 
dozens of gravediggers in orange coveralls have buried between 
5000 and 6000 victims in trench graves an official at the 
cemetery said wednesday 
we are still pulling out bodies from the debris said the 
official who asked not to be identified about two acres have been 
added to the half acre of cemetery in the past week 
at first we had to bury some people in unmarked mass graves 
three deep because there were so many and it was so hot said the 
cemetery supervisor 
in the new graves 5inchthick white stones are set on end to 
form a low wall down the middle of the trench the victims are 
buried down each side of the trench about a foot apart 
a refrigerator truck carrying 67 shrouded bodies in ice waited 
next to two 100footlong trenches for relatives to arrive for 
funerals 
the official said it was difficult contacting the relatives and 
he was unsure how long it would be before the funerals took place 
