the nations most populous state may not shift its presidential 
primary after all 
four months ago california was on the brink of shaking up the 
presidential nomination system by making its primary one of the 
earliest in the country 
a bill to move the presidential primary from early june to the 
first tuesday in march had passed both houses of the legislature in 
different forms 
some supporters were predicting that delegaterich california 
