the measure also would extend for two years the 124875 ceiling 
on fhainsured mortgages that congress last year raised from 
101250 in most highcost areas 
housing secretary jack kemp joined senate sponsors earlier 
wednesday in announcing a bipartisan agreement on key elements of 
the bill which represents the biggest revamping of federal housing 
