5 percent down payment and would be required to pay at least 
twothirds of closing costs up front without financing loans with 
low down payments deemed most at risk to default would be subject 
to an added annual fee 
under the compromise according to lawmakers the up front costs 
to a young family in a typical case buying their first home 
with an fhainsured mortgage would rise from 3500 to 4400 
borrowers currently can finance all closing costs sometimes 
resulting in loans greater than the value of the home on 
fhabacked mortgages 
