<TEXT>
the peace contentment and good will 
in renfro valley have been shaken 
the picturesque hollow that the late entertainer john lair 
described in his song the valley where time stands still is now 
the scene of a battle over rights to its name 
lair turned the valley 50 miles south of lexington into an 
entertainment center when he founded the renfro valley barn dance 
in 1939 his song described the valley as a place of peace and 
content and good will 
but that began to change last year when three investors bought 
the 110acre property that lair had trademarked and copyrighted 
the new owners renfro valley folks inc plan to turn the complex 
near interstate 75 into a 35 million countrymusic theme park 
the investors maintain that the purchase included the exclusive 
use of the renfro valley name 
several business owners in the unincorporated hamlet of about 75 
people balked when the new owners ordered them to stop using the 
words renfro valley in store names and merchandise 
