air traffic controllers in the chicago area 
allowed eight close calls between airplanes in a recent 10day 
period the federal aviation administration said 
one of the most serious involved two northwest airlines jets 
both flying at 33000 feet which came within ninetenths of a mile 
of each other according to a preliminary faa investigation 
