<TEXT>
president bush on thursday officially asked 
the senate to ratify the agreement he made with soviet president 
mikhail gorbachev on underground nuclear weapons tests 
the accord signed by the two countries june 1 during gorbachevs 
visit to washington spells out measures against cheating on 
existing treaties that limit nuclear tests 
the agreement will permit both nations to ratify the 1974 
threshold test ban treaty and the 1976 peaceful nuclear explosion 
treaty which limits us and soviet underground nuclear tests to 
150 kilotons 
the accords recently agreed to by the two countries represent 
the successful culmination of several years of effort to provide 
for effective verification of compliance with the treaties bush 
said in his letter transmitting the treaty protocols to the senate 
changes at the us nuclear test site in nevada that are 
required to meet the agreement were considered carefully and have 
been judged manageable and therefore acceptable in the interests of 
effective verification bush wrote 
</TEXT>
