1984 of the old bell system primarily because of fccordered 
reductions in local access charges 
the fcc last week ordered the nations local telephone companies 
to reduce by 11 billion effective sunday what they charge 
longdistance companies to connect with local phone networks 
longdistance carriers typically pass along to their customers 
savings from these reduced access charges 
other longdistance companies such as mci and us sprint 
usually follow atampts lead in rate reductions 
