that amount to the 11 billion figure 
before july 1989 when atampts earnings were restricted to about 
a 12 percent rate of return on its investments the company passed 
on to its customers nearly all the savings whenever local phone 
companies reduced their access charges 
but atampt now is under a regulatory scheme that controls its 
prices within a prescribed range of caps tied to the rate of 
inflation not its profits last november atampt raised prices for 
night and weekend calling by 13 percent 
