<TEXT>
twice a week clad in a filmy purple gown 
wearing deathly white makeup and a heavy black wig lee meriwether 
stands outside a sound stage and waves at the passing trams of the 
universal studios tour 
this is not a common occurrence on the tour few wellknown 
actors deign to make an appearance but meriwether star of the 
syndicated program the munsters today enjoys the attention 
it started when i was standing outside the stage one day when 
a tram came by the tour guide told them who i was i waved at 
them and they got a kick out of it she said 
one day a tram load of japanese tourists came by and nearly 
tilted over as everyone rushed to the side to take pictures said 
meriwether i wish id had a camera to take a picture of that 
meriwether is now at work on the third season of the munsters 
today a revival of the 1960s comedy series the original was 
something of a copy itself coming as it did on the heels of the 
popular show the addams family it was then and still is a 
spoof of domestic family sitcoms 
the munsters live at 1313 mockingbird lane in a musty gothic 
mansion each member of the family looks like a refugee from a 
horror flick 
herman the father is a gravedigger and dead ringer for 
frankensteins monster grandpa who looks like dracula tinkers 
with inventions in the basement 
the children are eddie a teenager who seems to be on his way 
to turning into a werewolf and marilyn a pretty young woman in 
the original show the rest of the munsters thought marilyn was 
abnormal and pitied her 
meriwethers lily is a vampire lily is basically your 
everyday mother in a sitcom said meriwether who was miss 
america in 1955 she adores her children she just looks 
different 
the actress revels in the shows monsterisms when she found a 
transylvania cookbook she bought dozens and gave them to friends 
the show has been brought up to date meriwether said the 
children have changed the most eddie no longer dresses in the 
little lord fauntleroy clothes he dresses as other teens do today 
we no longer worry about marilyns looks there was some talk 
that i would get a job 
the series features john schuck as herman howard morton as 
grandpa jason marsden as eddie and hillary van dyke as marilyn 
the original show broadcast on cbs from 196466 starred fred 
gwynne as herman yvonne decarlo as lily al lewis as grandpa 
butch patrick as eddie and beverly owen and later pat priest as 
marilyn 
meriwether did not give the munsters today much chance for 
survival 
first she said i thought it would be just a pilot i never 
thought it would become a series then i didnt think it would go 
beyond the first year 
it is now seen on more than 100 stations 
meriwether is a television veteran she had recurring roles on 
mission impossible dr kildare the fbi and 12 
oclock high as well as the time tunnel the new andy 
griffith show and barnaby jones 
in the last show she played betty jones the daughterinlaw of 
the eponymous character played by buddy ebsen that show originally 
was an episode of cannon but before they had completed the 
filming it became a spinoff and a new series it ran for eight 
seasons on cbs 
