the proposal ran into flak from domenici and house ways and 
means committee chairman dan rostenkowski dill people at the 
meeting said rostenkowski told his fellow negotiators that 
death would be the political consequence of adopting the idea 
other options discussed included 
boosting from 50 percent to 85 percent the amount of income 
subject to federal taxes earned by couples receiving social 
security and earning more than 32000 annually the increase would 
raise 31 billion for the government next year and 54 billion 
over five years 
medicare reductions 
cuts in spending on various federal employee benefit programs 
house majority leader richard gephardt dmo the lead 
democratic negotiator said there was a consensus that bargainers 
should try to concoct a plan that would balance the budget by 
fiscal 1995 
that would be two years after the grammrudman law requires the 
deficit to be eliminated 
its fair to assume that the targets are going to be 
changed domenici said 
outside the bargaining room however members of both parties 
clung to partisan positions on the questions of taxes 
sen trent lott rmiss and 12 of his 44 senate gop colleagues 
signed a letter saying the deficit must be controlled through 
spending reductions and economic growth not through tax 
increases 
on tuesday 90 of the 176 house republicans signed a similar 
note 
democratic leaders said they remained unconcerned about the 
petitions saying unhappy lawmakers might change their minds if tax 
hikes were part of a solid deficitreduction package that included 
spending cuts 
but other democrats sought to use the gop disarray to their 
partys advantage 
how is the president going to lead the country if he cant 
lead his own party rep charles schumer dny asked on the 
house floor 
