<TEXT>
the declining presence of coffee in american 
diets has marketers scrambling for ways to attract younger drinkers 
and to expand in overseas markets 
the impact of the decadeslong slide in us coffee drinking was 
highlighted wednesday when maxwell house announced plans to close a 
50yearold coffee roasting and grinding plant in hoboken nj 
the company a division of philip morris cos kraftgeneral 
foods international blamed declining consumption for the move 
americans drank an average of 175 cups of coffee per person 
last year down from a peak in 1962 of 312 cups per day according 
to the londonbased international coffee organization the 
organization represents coffeeproducing countries such as brazil 
and colombia 
people are moving from hot acrid drinks to sweet cold 
drinks i think they will continue to do so because of our 
lifestyle people dont want to sit around blowing on coffee or 
