<TEXT>
american telephone and telegraph co said 
thursday it will reduce its evening interstate longdistance rates 
by about 5 percent and daytime rates by about a halfpercent on 
july 1 as part of a 300 million overall price cut 
the company also will reduce the prices of operatorassisted 
calls uscanada calls and its reach out america optional 
longdistance calling plan 
overall interstate calling rates will go down an average 22 
percent atampt spokesman herb linnen said 
the cost of a 10minute directdial evening call anywhere in the 
country will drop to 149 from 158 
the cuts require approval by the federal communications 
commission 
the fcc last week ordered the nations local telephone companies 
to reduce by 11 billion effective july 1 what they charge 
longdistance companies to connect with local phone networks 
longdistance carriers typically pass along to their customers 
savings from these reduced access charges 
other phone companies such as mci and us sprint usually follow 
suit to remain competitive 
atampt the nations largest longdistance company had announced 
last month it would cut its rates by 160 million annually based 
upon earlier requests that local phone companies had made with the 
fcc 
the local companies in april had asked to reduce their access 
charges by just 405 million on july 1 but the fcc last week 
increased that amount to the 11 billion figure 
before july 1989 when atampts earnings were restricted to about 
a 12 percent rate of return on its investments the company passed 
on to its customers nearly all the savings whenever local phone 
companies reduced their access charges 
but atampt now is under a regulatory scheme that controls its 
prices within a prescribed range of caps tied to the rate of 
inflation not its profits last november atampt raised prices for 
night and weekend calling by 13 percent 
atampts residential and small business prices currently are right 
at the cap so the july 1 reductions were needed linnen said 
large business prices are well below the caps he said 
atampt said that on july 1 it will cut prices for 
directdial interstate calls between 5 pm and 11 pm sunday 
through friday by an average 5 percent 
daytime 8 am to 5 pm directdial calls by an average 05 
percent 
reach out america evening discount plan from 815 to 780 per 
hour a month and reach out halfhour plan to 4 to 435 
perminute operatorassisted calls an average 3 percent 
the first minute of canadian calls at all times 
the company said it would eliminate the one free call now 
allowed to interstate directory service meaning all such calls 
will cost 60 cents each 
atampts prices have dropped nearly 43 percent since the 1984 of 
the old bell system primarily because of fccordered reductions in 
access charges 
