<TEXT>
toyota motor corp said thursday it plans to buy 
about 76 million worth of semiconductor components made by us 
manufacturers over the next three years 
the japanese carmaker also said it selected five us 
semiconductor manufacturers to make custom electronics components 
for toyota vehicles toyota said the agreements are part of its 
drive to increase the amount of us electronics it uses 
the five companies are intel corp international rectifier 
corp motorola inc national semiconductor corp and texas 
instruments inc 
toyota officials announced the agreements in new york and 
washington after completing their second mission to the united 
states in search of electronics suppliers 
the five companies will work with toyota to develop 23 types of 
electronic components including custom computer chips that control 
automobile suspension systems engines instruments and stereo 
systems the agreements could result in more than 17 million worth 
of sales over a threeyear period beginning april 1 1991 toyota 
said 
hiroshi arai general manager of toyotas electronics 
engineering division said the company began to buy us 
semiconductors last year those sales were of offtheshelf 
semiconductor products as opposed to the custom chips envisioned 
under the new agreements 
we would like to begin on a small scale and build up to a big 
business he told reporters speaking through a translator our 
impression is that we have been able to develop very good teamwork 
with the us semiconductor manufacturers 
about half of the types of custom components to be purchased 
from the five us companies would cost slightly less if they were 
obtained from japanese suppliers arai said he encouraged us 
chip makers to improve their manufacturing efficiency to cut costs 
toyota would not say how much it intended to spend on each 
companys products 
james edson a motorola marketing official said the new 
agreements represent an advancement over last years pacts which 
included purchases from motorola because the components to be 
purchased are more sophisticated 
the components motorola will supply will be made throughout the 
world including japan edson said motorola based in schaumburg 
ill is the worlds largest supplier of semiconductors for 
automotive use 
though he praised motorolas relationship with toyota edson 
said toyota is not motorolas largest customer among japanese 
carmakers he said he could not reveal the other company 
millard phelps a technology analyst at the san francisco 
brokerage hambrecht amp quist inc said the automobile industry 
represents an important market for us electronics companies 
although automotive uses account for less than 10 percent of 
us semiconductor production the percentage is growing rapidly as 
automobile control devices become more sophisticated he said 
