copper futures prices rose sharply thursday on new yorks 
commodity exchange amid speculation of a strike at an arizona 
copper mine and supply disruptions from zambia the worlds 
sixthlargest copper producer 
on other commodity markets precious metals orange juice and 
energy futures advanced grains and soybeans were mixed and 
livestock and meat futures were mixed 
copper futures settled 31 cents to 5 cents higher with the 
contract for delivery in july up 43 cents at 1143 a pound 
analysts said most of the buying was caused by the threat of a 
strike at asarco incs ray copper mine which produces 115000 
tons of copper concentrate per year 
workers have set a strike deadline of midnight saturday and 
analysts saw little hope for a new contract agreement before then 
the mines production is substantial but the market is in a 
period of seasonally slow demand and could weather a strike of two 
or three weeks comfortably said james steel a metals analyst with 
refco inc in new york 
it wouldnt matter but thats not the way the market 
reacted he said 
copper prices also were supported by continuing unrest in 
zambia where about two dozen people have died this week in riots 
sparked by the governments abolition of food subsidies 
the disturbances have not occurred in zambias two major 
coppermining areas but there is speculation the rioting might 
spread steel said 
in precious metals trading on the commodity exchange gold 
futures settled 70 cents to 80 cents higher with august at 35410 
a troy ounce silver was 12 cents to 18 cents higher with july at 
4813 a troy ounce 
orange juice futures surged on the new york cotton exchange as 
the market continued recovering from last weeks technically 
inspired collapse thursdays rally accelerated after the july 
contract surpassed 185 a pound the price level that some 
analysts had cited as the trigger for the recent sharp decline 
frozen concentrated orange juice settled 195 cents to 57 cents 
higher with july at 1879 a pound 
