made in a deal with federal prosecutors that resulted in us 
district judge alicemarie h stotler dismissing three other fraud 
charges against the company 
as part of the deal in federal court in santa ana the 
government also agreed to drop its case against swedlow vice 
president norman gene nixon if after one year he is not convicted 
of any other crime 
nixon and the company were charged with scheming to misrepresent 
the seriousness of defects in four windshields swedlow lawyer 
dennis kinnard said the company believed the indictment was unfair 
because the flaws were too minor to impair the windshields fitness 
for flight 
