pathe communications corp said 
thursday its attempt to get a loan from time warner inc had 
stalled and it would look elsewhere for money to buy mgmua 
communications co for 13 billion 
time warners failure to lend pathe 650 million is the latest 
setback to efforts by kirk kerkorian mgmuas controlling 
shareholder to sell the company 
pathe spokesman craig parsons said the company was looking at 
a broad universe of options for raising the rest of the money 
it could take any shape equity financing investors 
parsons said theyre confident despite how this might be 
perceived by others pathe has already made 200 million in cash 
down payments to mgmua 
rumors had flown for weeks that time warner would decide against 
making the loan 
in the two years kerkorian has had mgmua on the auction block 
nearly every big entertainment and media company has examined its 
assets australias qintex group agreed to buy mgmua for 15 
billion last year but was unable to arrange financing media mogul 
rupert murdoch who had offered 14 billion declined to reenter 
the bidding 
the time warner loan had been a centerpiece of pathes original 
12 billion 20pershare offer for mgmua time warner was to 
have gotten a lien on the united artists library as security plus 
distribution rights to the library and future pathe and mgm movies 
but pathes chief italian financier giancarlo parretti and 
kerkorian negotiated a new deal last week the new deal was crafted 
when parretti was unable to meet a saturday deadline for arranging 
the rest of the financing to time warners satisfaction the new 
deal raised the offer by 100 million to 13 billion 
time warner had insisted that pathe put at least 450 million in 
equity into the deal plus 150 million in equity from outside 
sources pathe instead proposed to raise funds primarily by 
borrowing money from european affiliates although it said it 
intended to convert that debt to equity by issuing stock to the 
affiliates 
the new buyout bid which was finalized thursday structured the 
deal as a merger rather than a tender offer and made no mention of 
time warner 
pathe intends to continue a dialogue with time warner pathe 
said in a brief statement it added pathe will seek alternative 
sources of financing to conclude its acquisition of mgmua 
mgmua spokesman scott tagliarino said mgmua would have no 
comment on the latest announcement he noted that so far pathe has 
made all its goodfaith payments 
kerkorian already had surrendered most of the control over his 
studio to qintex when that deal fell apart over a 50 million down 
payment determined not to be burned again he has made his 
agreements with parretti contingent upon a series of monthly 50 
million payments of which parretti has made four beginning in 
march 
another 53 million is due this month it and the 200 million 
in previous down payments will be distributed to mgmua 
stockholders as a 4pershare payment 
parretti has agreed to make additional 50 million payments in 
august and september and come up with the balance of the money by 
oct 23 
investors have been skeptical about the chances of the deal 
going through at its current level of 2150 per share mgmua 
stock closed thursday at 1787 up 12 cents per share on the 
new york stock exchange before pathe announced its negotiations 
with time warner had stalled 
